CatDescriptText: Miss Lorraine Dominick, business training college student, 2143 Waring Court, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 24, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that President Eisenhower should invoke the Taft-Hartley Act in steel strike?" answer reads: "Yes. The strike is having too much affect on business and industry.  And if it is not settled, everything will be affected."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Lorraine Dominick wearing dark cardigan, chain necklace, and light colored overcoat, holding zippered binder, standing in front of Beck Shoes, Fifth Avenue, Downtown
